1️⃣Docker Network
Docker Network allows:
Containers to communicate with each other internally
Without exposing ports to host machine.(or to each other c2c)
with help of isolated networks.

🧠 Default Network Types in Docker

Docker provides 3 main network drivers:

Network   	Purpose
bridge    	Default, container-to-container communication
host	      Uses host network directly
none	      No network

🎯 Port binding using -p is required only when exposing a container service to the host machine. 
Containers on the same Docker network communicate internally using private IPs and Docker’s internal DNS, so no port binding is needed between them.

📦 How This Works Internally
No -p needed.
Because:
Docker creates virtual bridge
Assigns private IPs
Provides internal DNS
Containers talk using name → IP mapping
This is internal networking.

There is still a port inside the container.
Example:
nginx runs on port 80.

But:
Containers directly access container_name:80
No host port mapping required

